Package org.qscript

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Argument
    An argument represents a dynamically typed un-named value and is used to store the intermediate and final results of an expression evaluation.
    Complex
    Immutable class used to represent complex numbers.
    The original authors and origin of this class has been lost in time but it has been modified to make it immutable by Peter Lager 2014
    FlowAction
    When a FlowOperator is evaluated it returns a FlowAction object indicating the next step to be evaluated.
    Result
    A Result object is created when an expression or algorithm has been evaluated.
    Script
    This class is responsible for managing all the actions necessary to evaluate an expression or algorithm.
    ScriptStep
    This class wraps up the token together with information about where to go once it has been evaluated.
    Solver
    This class has static methods to provide a simple API for users to evaluate an expression or script in the main process thread.
    Solver$
    This class is similar to Solver in that it has static evaluate() methods to evaluate an expression or script, but now done in its own thread.
    Thing
    This class is the key to extending QScript to work with and manipulate user defined clases.
    Token
    This is the base class for operators and arguments.
    Variable
    This is a type of 'argument' but has an identifier which can be used in an algorithm to access the value.
    Vector
    Immutable representation of a Vector.
